JOHANNESBURG - South Africans have been asked to help Miss SA Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters grab the Miss Universe crown at the competition on Sunday, November 26 in Las Vegas. Pre-voting for the pageant has already opened and will close on November 25. Fans will also get an opportunity to vote during the live broadcast for each round of the competition. South Africans can cast their ballots by going to Vote.MissUniverse.com. Each person can vote up to 10 times a day. Fans can also vote on Twitter using the hashtags #MissUniverse and #SouthAfrica. Retweets will count towards the final tally. The competition will be broadcast live on Vuzu (DStv Channel 116) at 05:00 (CAT). GALLERY: Highlights from the 2017 Miss World Pageant eNCA